title: O'Leary steps down as UCF AD
text:
George O'Leary steps down as interim AD at UCF Football team falls to 0-6 with loss to UConn Published On: 39 m Updated 29 m Tweet ORLANDO, Fla. - 
University of Central Florida head football coach George O'Leary will step down as the school's interim athletic director, sources confirmed Monday to News 6 sports director David Pingalore. 
The announcement comes days after UCF fell to 0-6 on the season with a 40-13 loss to the University of Connecticut. Quick Clicks 
O'Leary replaced Todd Stansbury, who accepted the athletic director position at Oregon State over the summer. 
UCF plays at Temple on Saturday night.
